<task id="AUTHV2-060" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add CSP + Trusted Types middleware on BFF</title>
    <phase>D — Reasonable security hardening</phase>
    <tags>security, server, csp, xss, FULL</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>Phase C</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>D-Parallel-1</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>localStorage tokens are only as safe as XSS defense. Add strict CSP headers + Trusted Types on BFF responses serving HTML/JS. Code Pages hosted in Dataverse get appropriate CSP via Dataverse env config (document separately).</prompt>
  <role>Security-focused .NET engineer.</role>
  <goal>Strict CSP: script-src 'self', no inline, no eval. Trusted Types enforced in production builds. Customer security questionnaires can answer "yes, strict CSP".</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md §"What they'd push back on" #3 (XSS posture)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Implement SecurityHeadersMiddleware that adds CSP + Trusted Types headers on every response.</step>
    <step>CSP: `default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://login.microsoftonline.com https://graph.microsoft.com; frame-ancestors https://*.dynamics.com https://*.crm.dynamics.com;`. Tune per actual needs.</step>
    <step>Trusted Types: `require-trusted-types-for 'script'`. Use Report-Only initially to surface violations without breaking.</step>
    <step>Add HSTS, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy headers.</step>
    <step>Wire middleware first in pipeline.</step>
    <step>Test via curl + browser: verify headers present.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>SecurityHeadersMiddleware adds CSP + Trusted Types + HSTS + supporting headers.</criterion>
    <criterion>CSP policy documented + tunable.</criterion>
    <criterion>Trusted Types in Report-Only mode initially.</criterion>
    <criterion>BFF endpoints work without CSP-induced breakage.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
